        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How the LLM Selects Tools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you pass a list of tools to an LLM, it reads the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "name",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "description",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and property descriptions of each tool, then decides \u2014 based on the conversation \u2014 whether to call a tool, which tool to call, and what arguments to pass. This is a purely semantic decision made inside the model's forward pass; there is no explicit retrieval or routing step."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The decision process roughly mirrors how a human reads an API docs page: find the function whose description best matches the task at hand, read the parameter docs, fill in the values from context. The quality of the tool's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "description",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the single biggest determinant of correct tool selection."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "If the LLM picks the wrong tool or calls no tool when it should, fix the description first. Clarify when to use it and when NOT to use it."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The tool_choice Parameter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "All major providers expose a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "tool_choice",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter that controls whether and how the LLM uses tools. The options are consistent across OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google Gemini, though the exact syntax varies by SDK."
          }
        ]
      },
