      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from openai import OpenAI\nclient = OpenAI()\n\ntools = [get_weather_tool, search_tool, calendar_tool]\n\n# auto: let the LLM decide\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the weather in Paris?\"}],\n    tools=tools,\n    tool_choice=\"auto\",\n)\n\n# required: LLM must call something\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Extract the city from: 'Weather in Paris looks great'\"}],\n    tools=[extract_city_tool],\n    tool_choice=\"required\",\n)\n\n# Force a specific tool (structured extraction)\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Parse: 'Meeting on June 15 at 2pm'\"}],\n    tools=[parse_datetime_tool],\n    tool_choice={\"type\": \"function\", \"function\": {\"name\": \"parse_datetime\"}},\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reading the LLM Response"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A tool call response has a different structure from a normal text response. Always check "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "finish_reason",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " before accessing message content. When the LLM calls tools, "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "finish_reason",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"tool_calls\"",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "message.content",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is typically empty; the tool calls are in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "message.tool_calls",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from openai import OpenAI\nimport json\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the weather in Paris and London?\"}],\n    tools=tools,\n    tool_choice=\"auto\",\n)\n\nchoice = response.choices[0]\nprint(f\"finish_reason: {choice.finish_reason}\")\n\nif choice.finish_reason == \"tool_calls\":\n    for tc in choice.message.tool_calls:\n        print(f\"Tool: {tc.function.name}\")\n        print(f\"Args: {tc.function.arguments}\")\n        args = json.loads(tc.function.arguments)\n        # dispatch...\n\nelif choice.finish_reason == \"stop\":\n    # LLM chose to respond with text instead\n    print(choice.message.content)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parallel Tool Calling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the LLM can answer a request by calling multiple tools independently, it may return several tool calls in a single response. All calls appear in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "message.tool_calls",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " as a list. Run them in parallel, collect all results, then pass everything back to the LLM in a second call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nimport asyncio\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\n\nclient = AsyncOpenAI()\n\nasync def call_tool(tc) -> dict:\n    args = json.loads(tc.function.arguments)\n    if tc.function.name == \"get_weather\":\n        result = get_weather(**args)\n    elif tc.function.name == \"get_stock_price\":\n        result = get_stock_price(**args)\n    else:\n        result = {\"error\": f\"Unknown tool: {tc.function.name}\"}\n    return {\n        \"tool_call_id\": tc.id,\n        \"role\": \"tool\",\n        \"content\": json.dumps(result),\n    }\n\nasync def run_parallel_tools():\n    messages = [\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the weather in Paris and MSFT's stock price?\"}\n    ]\n\n    # First LLM call\n    response = await client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n        messages=messages,\n        tools=tools,\n        tool_choice=\"auto\",\n    )\n\n    assistant_msg = response.choices[0].message\n    tool_calls = assistant_msg.tool_calls\n\n    if not tool_calls:\n        return assistant_msg.content\n\n    # Run all tool calls in parallel\n    tool_results = await asyncio.gather(*[call_tool(tc) for tc in tool_calls])\n\n    # Second LLM call with all results\n    messages.append(assistant_msg)\n    messages.extend(tool_results)\n\n    final = await client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n        messages=messages,\n        tools=tools,\n    )\n    return final.choices[0].message.content\n\nprint(asyncio.run(run_parallel_tools()))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Writing Tool Descriptions That Guide Selection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The LLM selects tools by matching the user's intent to tool descriptions. A weak description leads to missed calls, wrong tool selection, or the LLM generating an answer from memory instead of calling the appropriate tool."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
